vements within nineteenth-century America and attempted to address questions still relevant to today's society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aClergyzMassachusettszBostonvBiography. 0aOutdoor lifezUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aOutdoorsmenzUnited StatesvBiography. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Philosophy. 4aGeneral Interest : Biography. 4aGeneral Interest : General Interest. 4aLiterature : Nineteenth-Century Studies. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848936040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438489360423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438489360/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles